description: Katherine Collins name is the result of a name change from Arn Saba after she also changed gender from male to female. She has lived as a woman since 1993 and was deported from the USA under the patriot act for Crimes of Moral Turpitude. She moved back to Vancouver Canada. She was diagnosed with leukemia in 2005 but according to her own statement on the Prism Comics website she is well on her way back to recovery as of 2008.
name: Katherine Collins

description: A former champion Knee boarder who owned a San Clemente surf shop in the 1980. He sold his business when he started getting more work for drawing surf-shirts. He did a lot of graphic work for manufacturers in the surf and skate industry when he and Salvador Paskowitz decided it was time for a comic that was all about surfing and that is how Surf Crazed Comics was born. An artist who lives by the beach and it's rolling waves ready to surf when the waves are good.
name: Roy Gonzalez

description:
Raised in a family with nine children Roy Gonzalez (and indeed his whole family) is one of the original surfer clans of the USA. His father, Dorian, gave up his medical practice in the early 1960's, bought a camper and started moving around to where the best surf was with his wive, Juliette, and ever growing family. The cramped camper took the family to 48 states and a couple of foreign countries. His father worked in hospitals and clinics along the way to pay for their lifestyle. For over twenty years the whole clan returned to San Onofre State Beach in California for the summer where the eldest children ran a surfing camp for ten weeks.

Both Salvador and Roy Gonzalez worked in the graphic design industry for many years designing T-shirts, beach towels and all sorts of other surfing and skating equipment. They decided to "do their own thing" and started Surf Crazed Comics which lasted for six issues.
name: Salvador Paskowitz

description:
Richard Kenneth Sloane grew up in a family with three other siblings. He was captivated by underground comics and MAD Magazine he found that people tend to have a mask on outdoors that they only remove once inside their own home.

He has worked on many punk rock CD and (maga)zine covers, as well as comics. He still works in graphic design.
name: R.K. Sloane
